09/07/2004
PARIS, France -- Foreign Minister Michel Barnier met with his Albanian counterpart, Kastriot Islami, on Thursday (8 July) in a bid to strengthen bilateral ties. The French government sent a strong message of support for democratic changes in Albania. "We wish to help Albania advance on the path of reforms which will bring it closer to the EU and NATO," read a statement from the French Foreign Ministry. Paris says Albania plays a major role in the Balkans, particularly in working to resolve the issue of Kosovo. (Albanian Daily News - 09/07/04)
